test: add comprehensive tests for duplicate rename conflict resolution
- Add test_multiple_files_rename_to_same_target_with_auto_rename: Verifies that when AI returns multiple matches that would result in the same target filename, the AutoRename conflict resolution correctly applies numeric suffixes sequentially - Add test_conflict_resolution_with_existing_target_files: Tests sequential conflict resolution when target files already exist, ensuring new files get higher numeric suffixes - Add test_move_mode_with_duplicate_rename_conflicts: Tests move mode with conflict resolution to ensure original files are properly moved with conflict-resolved names
These tests verify the behavior described in the user's question about how SubX handles scenarios where the AI answer list contains multiple files that would rename to the same target name. The tests confirm that: 1. Operations are processed sequentially to prevent direct conflicts 2. AutoRename strategy automatically resolves conflicts with numeric suffixes (.1, .2, etc.) 3. The system correctly handles both copy and move modes 4. Existing target files are preserved while new files get incremented suffixes
Follows testing guidelines with: - Complete test isolation using TestConfigService and TempDir - Dependency injection pattern throughout - Mock AI responses using wiremock framework - Comprehensive verification of file operations and content preservation
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: add missing request_timeout_seconds support in TestConfigService
- Add request_timeout_seconds field support in TestConfigService get_config_value method - Add request_timeout_seconds field support in TestConfigService validate_and_set_value method - Update ai_request_timeout_tests.rs to use correct error message format - All tests now pass successfully
The TestConfigService was missing support for the ai.request_timeout_seconds configuration field that was already implemented in ProductionConfigService. This fix ensures consistent behavior between test and production configuration services.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: resolve Bug 21 - match cache copy mode incorrect target directory
When executing followed by (without dry-run), subtitle files were incorrectly copied to the subtitle directory instead of the video file directory due to cache not recalculating relocation information during cache loading.
Changes: - Fix check_file_list_cache() to recalculate requires_relocation and relocation_target_path based on current relocation_mode - Add comprehensive test suite for Bug 21 verification - Ensure consistency between dry-run and actual execution behavior
The fix reuses existing calculation logic from match_file_list() to maintain consistency and reliability. All existing tests pass, confirming no regression in functionality.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: add bug plan for match command cache copy mode target directory issue
- Identified root cause: cache loading does not recalculate relocation_target_path and requires_relocation - Current cache stores complete file paths and original_relocation_mode - Solution: recalculate relocation info when loading from cache using current relocation_mode - Simplified approach: only modify check_file_list_cache function - Estimated completion: 3-4 working days - Risk level: low to medium
This bug causes subtitle files to be copied to subtitle directory instead of video directory when using cache from dry-run execution followed by actual execution in copy mode.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: add configurable HTTP request timeout for AI services
- Add request_timeout_seconds field to AIConfig with default 120s - Support timeout configuration via config service get/set methods - Enhance OpenAI client retry mechanism with detailed error logging - Provide specific guidance for timeout and connection errors - Add configuration validation (10-600 seconds range) - Update config documentation and usage analysis
This resolves timeout issues reported with slow network connections where OpenAI Dashboard shows successful responses but client times out. Users can now configure longer timeouts via: - Config file: ai.request_timeout_seconds = 180 - CLI: subx-cli config set ai.request_timeout_seconds 180
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

refactor(cli): simplify help messages and remove excessive documentation
- Simplified all CLI argument documentation comments to be concise - Removed verbose examples and detailed explanations from help text - Fixed missing documentation for struct fields (command, action) - Updated integration test to match new help message format - All help messages now display clean, essential information only
The CLI help output is now much more readable and user-friendly while maintaining all necessary information for users to understand command usage.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>
